The 1991 set of Omu-Aran Government Secondary school Old Boys Association, Irepodun Local Government Area of Kwara State has set aside N2m to assist members who are financially constraints. Speaking at the 30th reunion anniversary of the set held in Omu-Aran, Chairman of the set, Mr Rufus Oyedepo  who is also the chairman of the planning committee of the event said that the Association had also earmarked the sum of N1.5m for improving the school information and Communication Technology Unit with modern gadgets and equipment to aid teaching and learning in the school. “A member who had serious eye defect was recently bankrolled on a trip to India for necessary medical attention and we thank God the member is now better and sound.” He said that the re-union anniversary was been held simultaneously in other locations outside the country by Diaspora members in Texas, Chicago in USA, Canada and United Kingdom. 19 teachers including a former Principal, Mr George Adeniran were honoured with exceptional merit awards by the 1991 set. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com